# Autopus UX Helpers

> UX helper format specifications for categorized help, next-step detection, and error recovery.
> Agents MUST apply these formats in the described contexts.

---

## B1: Categorized Help Format

Use this categorized layout when displaying the subcommand list (e.g., on empty `/auto` invocation).

**개발 워크플로우**

| Subcommand | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| plan | Write a SPEC |
| go | Implement a SPEC |
| sync | Synchronize documentation |
| fix | Fix a bug |
| dev | Full cycle: plan → go → sync |

**품질 & 리뷰**

| Subcommand | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| review | Code review |
| spec review | SPEC multi-provider review |
| secure | Security audit |
| stale | Detect stale decisions |

**탐색 & 분석**

| Subcommand | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| map | Analyze codebase structure |
| why | Query decision rationale |
| status | SPEC dashboard |

**관리**

| Subcommand | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| setup | Generate project context |
| init | Initialize harness |
| update | Update harness |
| doctor | Health diagnostics |
| platform | Platform management |

**Natural language hint:**

> 자연어로 작업을 설명하면 난이도를 자동 분석하여 적절한 플로우를 추천합니다. (fix / plan --skip-prd / plan)

