## B3: Error Recovery Guide Format

Display when a Phase or subcommand fails.

```
✗ {Phase/subcommand} 실패: {error description}
  복구 옵션:
  1. {recovery command 1}
  2. {recovery command 2}
```

**Per-context templates:**

Validation failure (Gate 2):
```
✗ Validation 실패: {N}개 이슈 발견
  복구 옵션:
  1. /auto go {SPEC-ID} --continue  (중단점에서 재개)
  2. /auto fix "{specific issue}"   (개별 이슈 수정)
```

Review failure (Gate 3 — REQUEST_CHANGES):
```
✗ Review 실패: {N}개 변경 요청
  복구 옵션:
  1. /auto go {SPEC-ID} --continue  (수정 후 재개)
  2. /auto review                   (변경사항 직접 검토)
```

Subagent failure (executor/tester crash):
```
✗ {agent-name} 실패: {error description}
  복구 옵션:
  1. /auto go {SPEC-ID} --continue  (파이프라인 재개)
  2. {manual fallback instruction}  (수동 처리)
```

General subcommand failure:
```
✗ {subcommand} 실패: {error description}
  복구 옵션:
  1. 오류 내용을 확인하고 재시도: /auto {subcommand} {args}
  2. /auto doctor  (시스템 상태 진단)
```

**Rules:**
- Always show exactly 2 recovery options
- First option: retry/continue command
- Second option: alternative approach or diagnostic
- Keep error description concise (one line)
